  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reinforcing policies for community participation in World Heritage sites in the cluster</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main activity will be reoriented to tackle the new challenges brought by the COVID-19 pandemic as regards site management, with a specific focus on community participation. In the first semester 2021, a specific activity related to the impact of COVID-19 on the livelihoods of communities in and around World Heritage sites, to be selected by States Parties. The main objective is to draw on interesting and complementary experiences concerning effects and measures taken to manage the COVID-19 pandemic. Considering the current emergency, a second dimension to be tackled will be education and heritage.

The activity will aim at promoting cooperation and exchange of experiences among the countries of the cluster.</narrative>
  </description>
